 Summary 
 THIS IS A PUBLIC NOTICE: Please review further information below regarding posting. 
 
As an IT Specialist, you will serves as an Information Management Specialist and web developer to support the planning, development, implementation, and operations of the OGP Web Portfolio. 
 
Location of position:  GSA, Office of Government-wide Policy, Office of Integrity, and Access, Digital Strategies Division 
 
We are currently filling one vacancy, but additional vacancies may be filled as needed. 
 
 Responsibilities 
 This Notice is issued under direct-hire authority to recruit new talent to this occupations for which there is a severe shortage of candidates. This means that we can hire any qualified candidate, either from this notice or from any source. 
 
A few key facts about this DHA notice: 
 
 Current civil service employees will receive new appointments if selected under this Direct Hire Authority. 
 
 For more information on DHA, please visit http//www.opm.gov/directhire/index.asp. 
 
Duties: 
 
 Provides web developer expert advice to OGP leadership while conducting hands-on planning and development of a web presence for OGP-that to the extent practicable, exemplifies the state-of-the-art in efficiency and effectiveness of mission-critical programs. 
 Uses Jekyll for static site generation, including development and implementation of custom Jekyll layouts, in conformance with the US Design Standards and Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act to build and manage GSAâ€™s web portfolio on the Federalist.gov platform, and/or subsequent hosting environment that OGP selects. 
 Leverages experience architecting and developing web and digital services presence for large-scale organizations, high quality platforms and services that support major initiatives, and provides technical, policy, and programmatic guidance to the U.S. Government. 
 Provides good interpersonal skills including social skills such as active listening, the ability to collaborate and an overall good work ethic and positive attitude. 
 
 Travel Required 
 Occasional travel - You may travel to attend meetings or training.
